Brazelton: HELP IS WHAT
 THIS STORY IS ALL ABOUT.

00:01:30.000 --> 00:01:33.000
HELP, AND HOPE.

00:01:33.000 --> 00:01:35.000
IT'S ABOUT A GROUP OF KIDS

00:01:35.000 --> 00:01:38.000
WHO'VE COME HERE FROM SCHOOLS
 ACROSS THE COUNTRY.

00:01:38.000 --> 00:01:41.000
KIDS FROM SUBURBS,
 AND THE INNER CITY,

00:01:41.000 --> 00:01:45.000
ALL DIFFERENT, BUT WITH
 THE SAME UNHAPPY TALE.

00:01:45.000 --> 00:01:48.000
Boy: IN MY SCHOOL,
 IF I FINISH MY HOMEWORK

00:01:48.000 --> 00:01:50.000
AND I DON'T KNOW
HOW TO SPELL--

00:01:50.000 --> 00:01:52.000
SPELL SOMETHING,
THEY WILL YELL AT ME.

00:01:52.000 --> 00:01:54.000
- Brazelton: REALLY?
- YEAH, BIG TIME.

00:01:54.000 --> 00:01:57.000
Brazelton:
 THEY'VE HAD A LOT OF
 HEARTACHE IN THEIR YOUNG LIVES.

00:01:57.000 --> 00:01:59.000
Boy:
 I JUST THOUGHT
 I WAS A DUMB KID

00:02:00.000 --> 00:02:02.000
BECAUSE ALL THE OTHER PEOPLE

00:02:02.000 --> 00:02:05.000
KNEW HOW READ, WRITE,

00:02:05.000 --> 00:02:09.000
AND I WASN'T IN THEIR GRADE
SO I THOUGHT I'D NEVER PASS.

00:02:09.000 --> 00:02:11.000
WHO REMEMBERS WHAT
PARAPHRASING IS?

00:02:11.000 --> 00:02:13.000
Brazelton: BUT THESE KIDS
 AREN'T DUMB,

00:02:13.000 --> 00:02:15.000
NOT AT ALL.

00:02:15.000 --> 00:02:18.000
...THE QUESTION,
AND YOU MAKE IT...

00:02:18.000 --> 00:02:19.000
Veronica Kenney:
 KIDS COME TO LANDMARK

00:02:19.000 --> 00:02:22.000
BECAUSE THEY HAVE LANGUAGE-BASED
LEARNING DISABILITIES.

00:02:22.000 --> 00:02:25.000
THIS MEANS THAT THEY HAVE
DIFFICULTY WITH READING,

00:02:26.000 --> 00:02:29.000
WITH EXPRESSING THEMSELVES
ORALLY AND IN WRITING.

00:02:29.000 --> 00:02:32.000
ALL ASPECTS OF THE LANGUAGE AREA
ARE COMPROMISED.

00:02:32.000 --> 00:02:35.000
HOWEVER, THEY ARE BRIGHT.

00:02:35.000 --> 00:02:39.000
Brazelton:
 LEARNING DISABILITIES
 AREN'T JUST THE CHILD'S ISSUE.

00:02:39.000 --> 00:02:42.000
Lori Pugsley:
 WE KNEW IN FIRST GRADE
 REBECCA WAS DYSLEXIC.

00:02:42.000 --> 00:02:44.000
THE DYSLEXIA DOESN'T END
WHEN SCHOOL ENDS,

00:02:44.000 --> 00:02:46.000
IT DOESN'T END
AT THREE O'CLOCK,

00:02:46.000 --> 00:02:48.000
IT DOESN'T END
DURING THE SUMMER.
IT'S EVERY DAY,

00:02:49.000 --> 00:02:51.000
AROUND THE CLOCK THAT THEY
LIVE AND BREATHE IT.

00:02:51.000 --> 00:02:53.000
AND THEREFORE THE FAMILY
 LIVES AND BREATHES IT.

00:02:54.000 --> 00:02:57.000
Brazelton:
 THE CONSTANT STRESS
 CAN CHANGE A CHILD.

00:02:57.000 --> 00:03:00.000
Lori:
 WHAT WE SAW WITH REBECCA
 WAS THAT, UM...

00:03:00.000 --> 00:03:02.000
SHE STOPPED TAKING RISKS,
SHE STOPPED BEING OUTSPOKEN,

00:03:02.000 --> 00:03:04.000
SHE KIND OF
BECAME MORE QUIET.

00:03:04.000 --> 00:03:07.000
SO, UH, REBECCA, WHAT DID YOU
COME UP WITH FIRST?

00:03:07.000 --> 00:03:10.000
Lori: WE COULD SEE THIS
 DOWNWARD SPIRAL HAPPENING,

00:03:10.000 --> 00:03:12.000
AND IF WE DIDN'T STOP
 THIS DOWNWARD MOTION,

00:03:12.000 --> 00:03:14.000
WE WOULD NEVER
GET HER TO THE POINT

00:03:14.000 --> 00:03:16.000
WHERE SHE COULD BE
FUNCTIONING AND INDEPENDENT

00:03:17.000 --> 00:03:19.000
AND YOU KNOW,
SUCCESSFUL IN LIFE.

00:03:19.000 --> 00:03:20.000
( chattering )

00:03:20.000 --> 00:03:22.000
Bob Broudo:
 TYPICALLY, THE FAMILIES

00:03:22.000 --> 00:03:24.000
WHO ARE BRINGING
 THEIR CHILDREN TO LANDMARK,

00:03:24.000 --> 00:03:28.000
ARE FAMILIES WHO COLLECTIVELY
HAVE EXPERIENCED FAILURE.

00:03:28.000 --> 00:03:32.000
THEY'VE SEEN THEIR CHILDREN
BE UNSUCCESSFUL IN SCHOOL,

00:03:32.000 --> 00:03:35.000
HAVE DIFFICULTY MAKING FRIENDS
SOMETIMES BECAUSE OF THAT,

00:03:35.000 --> 00:03:37.000
AND THEY'VE SEEN THE WONDERFUL
SPIRIT IN THEIR CHILD

00:03:37.000 --> 00:03:39.000
BEGIN TO FADE AWAY

00:03:39.000 --> 00:03:43.000
AS THEY LOSE CONFIDENCE
IN THEMSELVES TO LEARN.

00:03:43.000 --> 00:03:44.000
Brazelton:
 IT'S HARD TO IMAGINE

00:03:45.000 --> 00:03:47.000
HOW HOPELESS
 THESE KIDS HAVE FELT.

00:03:47.000 --> 00:03:49.000
JUST LISTEN.

00:03:49.000 --> 00:03:51.000
I WAS ALWAYS FRUSTRATED
AND I ALWAYS BEHIND,

00:03:51.000 --> 00:03:53.000
AND I WAS ALWAYS LIKE
CATCHING UP,

00:03:53.000 --> 00:03:55.000
AND WHEN IT WAS TIME
TO TAKE TESTS,

00:03:55.000 --> 00:03:58.000
I WAS ALWAYS A WRECK AND I
COULDN'T GET UP  THE GRADES

00:03:58.000 --> 00:04:00.000
THAT MY CLASSMATES WERE UP TO,

00:04:00.000 --> 00:04:02.000
AND THAT MADE ME
 FEEL, LIKE, TERRIBLE.

00:04:02.000 --> 00:04:04.000
Chris:
 I DIDN'T HAVE A GREAT
 EXPERIENCE IN MY OLD SCHOOL.

00:04:04.000 --> 00:04:07.000
IT MADE ME FEEL BAD
 THAT ALL THE OTHER KIDS

00:04:07.000 --> 00:04:10.000
WEREN'T HAVING AS MUCH TROUBLE
WITH THIS AS I WAS,

00:04:10.000 --> 00:04:14.000
AND I THOUGHT THERE WAS
SOMETHING REALLY WRONG WITH ME.

00:04:14.000 --> 00:04:17.000
Tom:
 I WENT TO A SCHOOL
 WHERE IT WAS LIKE REALLY TOUGH.

00:04:17.000 --> 00:04:19.000
I STARTED OFF BEHIND
 AND I ENDED UP BEHIND.

00:04:19.000 --> 00:04:21.000
EVERY YEAR I THOUGHT
 I WAS GETTING A LITTLE BIT

00:04:21.000 --> 00:04:24.000
BETTER AND BETTER BUT I WAS
 ACTUALLY GETTING WORSE.

00:04:24.000 --> 00:04:26.000
I THOUGHT I WAS STUPID AND...

00:04:26.000 --> 00:04:30.000
I JUST DIDN'T FEEL
CONFIDENT WITH MYSELF.

00:04:30.000 --> 00:04:32.000
Brazelton:
 ALTHOUGH MANY KIDS

00:04:32.000 --> 00:04:34.000
HAVE THESE KINDS
 OF LEARNING PROBLEMS,

00:04:34.000 --> 00:04:37.000
FEW SCHOOL SYSTEMS
 ARE REALLY ABLE TO HELP.

00:04:37.000 --> 00:04:40.000
Broudo:
 BECAUSE THE STUDENTS
 WHO COME TO US ARE WOUNDED

00:04:40.000 --> 00:04:42.000
FROM THEIR EXPERIENCE
 IN THE LEARNING PROCESS,

00:04:42.000 --> 00:04:44.000
ONE OF OUR MAJOR TASKS
 IS TO BUILD SUCCESS.

00:04:45.000 --> 00:04:47.000
WE DON'T CARE
WHERE SUCCESS BEGINS,

00:04:47.000 --> 00:04:50.000
SO WE INVOLVE THE STUDENTS
IN A WIDE RANGE OF ACTIVITIES.

00:04:50.000 --> 00:04:53.000
ACADEMICS, SOCIAL,
 EXTRA-CURRICULAR, ATHLETIC,

00:04:53.000 --> 00:04:57.000
AND ALL OF THE PEOPLE
 TEACHING EVERYTHING
 ARE THE TEACHERS.

00:04:57.000 --> 00:04:59.000
THEY GET TO KNOW
 THE STUDENTS WELL.

00:04:59.000 --> 00:05:01.000
AND THEY FIND OUT
 WHAT MOTIVATES THE KIDS,

00:05:01.000 --> 00:05:03.000
AND THEN THEY DEAL
 WITH SUCCESS.

00:05:03.000 --> 00:05:05.000
THE FIRST SUCCESS
 MAY NOT BE IN THE CLASSROOM.

00:05:05.000 --> 00:05:07.000
IT COULD BE BECAUSE THEY
 JOINED ONE OF THE ACTIVITIES,

00:05:07.000 --> 00:05:09.000
AND THEY FEEL GOOD
 FOR THE FIRST TIME.

00:05:09.000 --> 00:05:12.000
IN SOME OF THE SCHOOLS
YOU CAN'T DO THOSE THINGS

00:05:12.000 --> 00:05:13.000
BECAUSE YOUR GRADES ARE SO LOW

00:05:13.000 --> 00:05:16.000
YOU CAN'T PARTICIPATE
IN EXTRA-CURRICULAR ACTIVITIES.

00:05:16.000 --> 00:05:18.000
SO THEY COME HERE AND WE FIND
 SOME WAY TO BUILD THEM UP.

00:05:18.000 --> 00:05:21.000
THIS STRATEGY WORKS.

00:05:21.000 --> 00:05:23.000
AS SOON AS THEY BEGIN
 TO TRUST AN ADULT

00:05:23.000 --> 00:05:27.000
WHO IS COACHING OR IS WORKING
 WITH THEM IN ANY OTHER WAY,

00:05:27.000 --> 00:05:30.000
THEY ALSO RELAX A LITTLE BIT
 MORE IN THE CLASSROOM.

00:05:30.000 --> 00:05:32.000
CAN YOU FIND "SHUTS"?

00:05:32.000 --> 00:05:35.000
Brazelton:
 THAT'S WHEN THE REAL
 LEARNING CAN BEGIN.

00:05:35.000 --> 00:05:37.000
THOUGH CONFIDENT
 IN OTHER AREAS,

00:05:37.000 --> 00:05:41.000
MOST KIDS WITH THESE DEFICITS
 CAN'T BREAK DOWN WORDS

00:05:41.000 --> 00:05:43.000
INTO THEIR SOUNDS
 OR PHONEMES.

00:05:43.000 --> 00:05:45.000
ALL RIGHT.

00:05:45.000 --> 00:05:47.000
IT'S THE WAY
 THEIR BRAINS ARE WIRED.

00:05:48.000 --> 00:05:50.000
THIS MAKES LEARNING
 TO READ AND WRITE

00:05:50.000 --> 00:05:52.000
INCREDIBLY DIFFICULT.

00:05:52.000 --> 00:05:54.000
"INBAUTIOUS,"
"INCAUTIOUS."

00:05:54.000 --> 00:05:56.000
THE TEACHERS AT LANDMARK

00:05:56.000 --> 00:05:59.000
DON'T LOCK THEMSELVES
 INTO ONE APPROACH.

00:05:59.000 --> 00:06:01.000
EVEN KIDS
 WITH SIMILAR PROBLEMS

00:06:01.000 --> 00:06:03.000
RESPOND TO
 DIFFERENT STRATEGIES.

00:06:03.000 --> 00:06:06.000
...AND CHANGE IT
TO A TONGUE SCRAPER.

00:06:06.000 --> 00:06:08.000
YES.  WHICH TONGUE SCRAPER
DO YOU HAVE IN MIND?

00:06:08.000 --> 00:06:10.000
BEFORE,
I COULDN'T READ AT ALL.

00:06:10.000 --> 00:06:14.000
WITH MY TUTORIAL TEACHER,
MISS HERBERT,

00:06:14.000 --> 00:06:18.000
SHE KNOWS ALL THE RIGHT STEPS

00:06:18.000 --> 00:06:21.000
TO MAKE SOMEBODY
 A BETTER READER.

00:06:21.000 --> 00:06:24.000
OHH, "SHUTS."

00:06:24.000 --> 00:06:27.000
Brazelton:
 THE RESULTS CAN BE
 NOTHING SHORT OF A MIRACLE.

00:06:27.000 --> 00:06:28.000
ALL RIGHT, JOHN,

00:06:28.000 --> 00:06:30.000
YOU WANNA READ
 THE REST OF THE TOP PART?

00:06:30.000 --> 00:06:33.000
- Brazelton:
  JOHN IS AN EXAMPLE.
- "A THESIS STATEMENT..."

00:06:33.000 --> 00:06:36.000
Woman:
 THEY ASKED ME, "WHY DO
 YOU WANT JOHN TO COME HERE?"

00:06:36.000 --> 00:06:39.000
I TOLD THEM, "I WANT JOHN
TO HAVE THE LOOK IN HIS EYE

00:06:39.000 --> 00:06:42.000
THAT THESE CHILDREN HAVE."

00:06:42.000 --> 00:06:45.000
Gene Hilliard:
 IT WAS ABOUT 17 MONTHS AGO

00:06:45.000 --> 00:06:48.000
WE CAME TO
 A MUTUAL AGREEMENT

00:06:48.000 --> 00:06:50.000
WITH THE SPECIAL ED
TEACHER THERE

00:06:50.000 --> 00:06:53.000
THAT REALLY,
IT WAS HOPELESS.

00:06:53.000 --> 00:06:56.000
THE THESIS STATEMENT WOULD BE
"APPLES COME IN MANY VARIETIES."

00:06:56.000 --> 00:06:57.000
Pat Hilliard: I SAID,
 "JOHN, IT'S OVER, HONEY.

00:06:57.000 --> 00:07:00.000
IT'S OVER.  WE'RE GONNA
 FIND YOU A PLACE."

00:07:00.000 --> 00:07:03.000
HE SAID, "HELP ME."
SO HE DROPPED OUT OF SCHOOL,

00:07:03.000 --> 00:07:06.000
AND WE WENT ON A SEARCH.

00:07:06.000 --> 00:07:09.000
AND NOW HERE WE ARE,
15, 16 MONTHS LATER.

00:07:09.000 --> 00:07:12.000
HE'S HAD FABULOUS
ACADEMIC SUCCESS,

00:07:12.000 --> 00:07:15.000
AND HE'S PRESIDENT
OF THE STUDENT COUNCIL.

00:07:15.000 --> 00:07:18.000
John: I GOT THE ATTENTION
 I NEEDED, THE AMOUNT
 OF HELP I NEEDED.

00:07:18.000 --> 00:07:21.000
I HAND THE STUFF IN
 AND FEEL SUCCESS,
 FEELING GOOD ABOUT MYSELF.

00:07:21.000 --> 00:07:23.000
"HIGH SCHOOL IS A VERY FUN TIME
 IN A PERSON'S LIFE."

00:07:24.000 --> 00:07:26.000
NOW I'M HAVING A BLAST
EVERY DAY.

00:07:27.000 --> 00:07:29.000
Brazelton: THERE ARE
 SO MANY STORIES LIKE JOHN'S.

00:07:29.000 --> 00:07:33.000
Ian:
 THINGS WEREN'T WORKING
 OUT, SO I CAME OUT HERE.

00:07:33.000 --> 00:07:34.000
GOT INVOLVED WITH SPORTS,

00:07:34.000 --> 00:07:36.000
LACROSSE.

00:07:36.000 --> 00:07:38.000
AND EVERYTHING SEEMS
TO BE GOING GREAT.

00:07:38.000 --> 00:07:40.000
THE TEACHERS HERE ARE AMAZING,

00:07:40.000 --> 00:07:42.000
THEY TRY THEIR HARDEST
 TO HELP US.

00:07:42.000 --> 00:07:44.000
THEY'LL HELP US DURING
 THEIR BREAKS, THEIR LUNCHES,

00:07:44.000 --> 00:07:47.000
AFTER SCHOOL.
 THEY COULD BE GOING HOME,

00:07:47.000 --> 00:07:48.000
INSTEAD THEY STAY HERE
 AND HELP US,

00:07:49.000 --> 00:07:51.000
AND THAT'S JUST AMAZING.
 I LOVE IT.

00:07:51.000 --> 00:07:54.000
IT'S A VERY MOTIVATING
POPULATION TO WORK WITH,

00:07:54.000 --> 00:07:57.000
BECAUSE THEY'RE SO BRIGHT.
ONCE THEY BEGIN TO UNDERSTAND

00:07:57.000 --> 00:07:59.000
HOW TO CRACK
 THE CODE OF LANGUAGE,

00:07:59.000 --> 00:08:02.000
THEY GET EXCITED AND THE
 TEACHERS GET EXCITED WITH THEM.

00:08:02.000 --> 00:08:05.000
THEY KNOW THEY'RE CHANGING
 THE LIVES OF THESE KIDS.

00:08:05.000 --> 00:08:06.000
( kids singing )

00:08:06.000 --> 00:08:09.000
Noelle:
 I'VE ALWAYS SANG
 SINCE I WAS YOUNGER.

00:08:09.000 --> 00:08:10.000
I'VE LOVED IT.

00:08:10.000 --> 00:08:13.000
AS MUCH AS I TRIED,
 AS HARD AS I COULD,

00:08:13.000 --> 00:08:15.000
I COULD NOT LEARN
 TO READ MUSIC.

00:08:15.000 --> 00:08:16.000
THEN WHEN I CAME HERE,

00:08:16.000 --> 00:08:19.000
I WAS SORT OF PUSHED GOING,
"COME ON, JUST DO IT."

00:08:19.000 --> 00:08:22.000
THEN WHEN I STARTED
TRYING OUT FOR STUFF

00:08:22.000 --> 00:08:24.000
I WAS SURPRISED
WHEN I GOT IT.

00:08:24.000 --> 00:08:27.000
AND SO I'M MORE INVOLVED
THAN I'VE EVER BEEN.

00:08:30.000 --> 00:08:33.000
I KNOW I'M SMART NOW BECAUSE

00:08:33.000 --> 00:08:37.000
I CAN READ, WRITE AND DO MATH.

00:08:39.000 --> 00:08:41.000
IT FEELS MUCH BETTER NOW
BECAUSE LAST TIME

00:08:41.000 --> 00:08:45.000
I DIDN'T KNOW
HOW TO DO TIMES...

00:08:45.000 --> 00:08:47.000
...PLUS ALGEBRA A LITTLE.

00:08:49.000 --> 00:08:51.000
Laura:
 SINCE I'VE COME HERE

00:08:51.000 --> 00:08:54.000
I HAVE LIKE-- I'LL DO SOMETHING
BUT I'LL SUCCEED IN IT.

00:08:54.000 --> 00:08:58.000
THEN I WANT TO DO A LITTLE
BIT MORE AND SUCCEED MORE.

00:08:59.000 --> 00:09:02.000
COLLEGE, THAT'S WHERE
I'M GOING. NEXT STEP.

00:09:05.000 --> 00:09:09.000
I'M MORE WILLING
TO TRY THINGS NOW.

00:09:09.000 --> 00:09:13.000
AND I'M NOT REALLY AFRAID
TO DO ANYTHING.

00:09:13.000 --> 00:09:15.000
( kids shouting )

00:09:17.000 --> 00:09:20.000
Ann Paton:
 IT'S JUST AMAZING TO SEE

00:09:20.000 --> 00:09:23.000
THIS PERSON THAT
WE CARE ABOUT SO MUCH

00:09:23.000 --> 00:09:28.000
HAVING... CHANGED THIS WAY.

00:09:28.000 --> 00:09:29.000
UH...

00:09:33.000 --> 00:09:34.000
UM...

00:09:34.000 --> 00:09:36.000
I REALLY HAVE THE FEELING

00:09:36.000 --> 00:09:38.000
THAT HER FUTURE
WILL BE BRIGHT

00:09:38.000 --> 00:09:41.000
BECAUSE OF BEING HERE.

